-- FACTBOX: Details of RHJ's concept for GM's Opel
-- 
-- Fri Jul 17, 2009 4:05am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/07/17/us-opel-rhj-bid-factbox-sb-idUSTRE56G1YU20090717

 

 (Reuters) - Below are the highlights of RHJ International's ( RHJI.BR ) "Project Beam" concept for General Motors unit Opel, a copy of which was obtained by Reuters on Friday: 

 CONSIDERATION AND OWNERSHIP - RHJ contributes 175 million euros at closing of the deal, plus 100 million on Dec 31, 2012, for 50.1 percent equity stake - GM has 39.9 percent stake, no cash contribution - Employees have 10 percent stake, contribution of 250-300 million euros savings per year ASSUMPTIONS - Royalty rate of 3.5 percent in years 2010-2012, thereafter 5 percent - 3.8 billion euros in loans guaranteed by German government, to be repaid by 2014 - No exit by RHJ or dividends until government-backed loans have been repaid in full HEADCOUNT - Overall headcount reduced by about 9,900 employees throughout Europe, of which 8.1 million in manufacturing - Antwerp closed in March 2010 - Bochum kept open but downsized to produce the new Zafira, reduction to two shifts up to 2011 - Eisenach idled and reopened in 2012 to produce Corsa HB3 - Luton downsized in case Renault takes out its volume, 25 million euros separation costs included in plan - Ruesselsheim downsized as volume is moved to Bochum - Zaragoza downsized in order to re-open Eisenach in 2012 FINANCIALS - Net sales/revenues projected to rise from 16.9 billion euros in 2009 to 17.8 billion in 2010, 20.6 billion in 2011, 23.3 billion in 2012, 24.1 billion in 2013, 23.6 billion in 2014 - EBITDA projected at -0.7 billion euros in 2009, 0.5 billion in 2010, 1.7 billion in 2011, 2.4 billion in 2012, 2.3 billion in 2013, 2.5 billion in 2014 (Reporting by  Gernot Heller ; Writing by  Noah Barkin )